## Troubleshooting

### Build fails on backend
- Check the **Build Logs** in Railway
- Common issue: missing system packages — the Dockerfile handles this
- If Tesseract fails: remove OCR deps temporarily, deploy, add back

### Build fails on frontend
- Make sure `next.config.js` has `output: "standalone"`
- Check that all import paths are correct
- The Dockerfile handles the multi-stage build

### Database connection fails
- Make sure `DATABASE_URL` references the Postgres service correctly
- Railway uses: `${{Postgres.DATABASE_URL}}` to reference other services
- The `config.py` handles `postgres://` to `postgresql+asyncpg://` conversion

### CORS errors
- Make sure `FRONTEND_URL` backend variable matches the actual frontend URL
- Make sure `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` frontend variable matches the actual backend URL

### App is slow to start
- Railway free tier services sleep after 30 min of inactivity
- First request takes ~15 seconds to wake up
- Keep-alive services like UptimeRobot can ping your health endpoint

### Memory/size limits
- Railway free tier: 1GB RAM, 1GB disk per service
- The backend Dockerfile with LibreOffice + Tesseract is ~1.5GB
- If build fails due to size, remove LibreOffice from Dockerfile (reduces conversions)

